A simple crossplatform 2D multiplayer shooter.

More infromation is available in the Wiki.

How to build under Microsoft Windows, Visual Studio 2008:
  1. Run "premake4.exe vs2008"
  2. Build build\blowmorph.sln.

How to build under Ubuntu Linux:
  1. Install SFML-2.0
     http://www.sfml-dev.org/download/sfml/2.0/
     See the instructions below

  2. Install FreeImage
     > sudo apt-get install libfreeimage-dev

  3. Install pugixml-1.2
     https://code.google.com/p/pugixml/
     See the instructions below

  4. Install ENetPlus.
     https://bitbucket.org/xairy/enet-plus

  5. Generate project files
     > ./premake4 gmake

  6. > cd build

  7. On x32 system:
     > make config=release32
     On x64 system:
     > make config=release64

How to install SFML-2.0:
  1. Install cmake
     > sudo apt-get install cmake
  2. Install the dependencies listed at http://www.sfml-dev.org/tutorials/2.0/compile-with-cmake.php
     > sudo apt-get install libpthread-stubs0-dev libgl1-mesa-dev libxrandr-dev libfreetype6-dev libglew-dev libjpeg8-dev libsndfile1-dev libopenal-dev
  3. Download SFML-2.0-sources.zip from http://www.sfml-dev.org/download/sfml/2.0/ and extract
  4. > cd SFML-2.0
  5. > cmake .
  6. > make
  7. > sudo make install

How to install pugixml-1.2:
  1. Download pugixml-1.2.tar.gz from https://code.google.com/p/pugixml/ and extract
  2. > cd pugixml-1.2/scripts
  3. > cmake .
  4. > make
  5. > sudo make install

How to start server:
  1. Set port in blowmorph/data/server.xml, default: 4242
  2. > ./server.sh

How to start client:
  1. Set server's port and ip in blowmorph/data/client.ini, default: 127.0.0.1:4242
  2. > ./client.sh
